         <div>
            <head>18.9.1881 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="48915">Etretat</placeName> September
      18. 1881. Sunday</p>
            <p>Dreadful storm going on this evening. The lightning is the finest I have
      ever seen, red, green, purple, sky blue, and reminds one of that described by
      <persName key="13061">Bulwer Lytton</persName> in his &#x201e;<name type="work" key="28422">Last days of Pompei</name>&#x201c; It is also raining hard and
      although it is calm till about 10 or 11 and till then there is not a breath of
      wind and the thunder is the only noise the wind rises in the night and blows
      with great fury </p>
         </div>
